<h2> Definition </h2>

@KJ{{five}}@KJ{{grade}} verbs form the potential by changing the final kana to the @HI{{e}}-row
and adding the suffix @HI{{ru}}.
<p></p>

@KJ{{ichi}}@KJ{{grade}} verbs form the potential by dropping the final @HI{{ru}}
and adding the suffix @HI{{rareru}}. This means that the potential form and
<a href="grammar-verb-formation-passive.html"> passive form </a> of @KJ{{ichi}}@KJ{{grade}} verbs
are identical and must be distinguished based on context.
<p></p>

The two irregular verbs conjugate as shown above.
<p></p>

All potential verbs conjugate into further forms as @KJ{{ichi}}@KJ{{grade}} verbs.
<p></p>

<h2> Notes </h2>

@HI{{wakaru}}, which already includes the meaning of possibility withion itself, does not form
a potential verb.
<p></p>

